WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.700
Oxford Bookworms, Starters

00:04.000 --> 00:11.000
Girl on a Motorcycle by John Escott, Read by Rick Adamson.

00:11.520 --> 00:17.640
Published and copyright, Oxford University Press 2000.

00:20.000 --> 00:25.000
Chapter 1. Is there a motel? 

00:25.100 --> 00:31.000
Kenny is going across America by bus. 

00:31.000 --> 00:39.000
One evening, in summer, his bus arrives in a little town in California.

00:39.160 --> 00:45.000
I want to stop here tonight, says Kenny to the bus driver.

00:45.160 --> 00:50.000
Is there a motel, do you know? 


00:50.100 --> 00:53.000
Yes. Says the bus driver. 

00:53.000 --> 00:57.000
There's a nice motel across the river.

00:57.100 --> 01:00.160
It's not expensive. 

01:00.260 --> 01:04.160
Is there a bus to San Francisco, tomorrow? 

01:04.260 --> 01:09.000
Asks Kenny. Yes, says the bus driver.

01:09.160 --> 01:13.080
There's a bus every day. 

01:13.180 --> 01:17.080
Kenny gets off the bus with his bag. 

01:21.000 --> 01:28.080
Chapter 2. Give me the money!

01:29.080 --> 01:38.400
In a street in Los Angeles, somebody is robbing a security guard outside a supermarket.

01:39.160 --> 01:44.060
The robber is sitting on a motorcycle and has a gun. 

01:44.160 --> 01:51.060
Give me the money! The robber tells the security guard. 

01:52.140 --> 02:01.000
OK, OK! Says the security guard, and gives the robber the money. 

02:01.000 --> 02:05.000
Then the robber rides away

02:05.100 --> 02:10.040
But a camera is taking pictures. 

02:10.140 --> 02:16.040
After the robbery, the supermarket manager phones the police.

02:16.160 --> 02:29.000
Yes, he says. A robbery. Yes, long blond hair, and with a motorcycle. 

02:29.100 --> 02:36.000
A man or woman? We don't know.

02:36.180 --> 02:45.080
Yes, we have some pictures. OK! Quickly.

02:49.080 --> 02:55.280
Chapter 3. Room 23. 

02:57.080 --> 03:04.080
In the little town, 50 kilometers away from Los Angeles. 

03:04.080 --> 03:08.108
Kenny goes into the motel and asks for a room.

03:10.360 --> 03:12.200
Room 23 

03:12.300 --> 03:14.500
Says the man at the desk. 

03:14.600 --> 03:17.000
He gives Kenny a key.

03:18.840 --> 03:23.480
Thank you. Says Kenny. And he goes up to his room.

03:24.200 --> 03:30.040
An hour later, Kenny comes down to eat. 

03:30.140 --> 03:34.040
I'm hungry, he thinks. 

03:34.140 --> 03:38.000
He sees a girl arrive on a motorcycle.

03:38.680 --> 03:42.680
She walks to the front desk, and the woman gives her a key.

03:42.680 --> 03:56.680
Room 17, says the woman at the desk. I think I know her face, thinks Kenny. Is she somebody famous?

03:57.640 --> 04:15.480
Chapter 4. Is it her? Early the next morning, Kenny puts on the TV in his room.

04:17.640 --> 04:22.820
A newsreader is talking about the supermarket robbery. 

04:22.920 --> 04:26.720
There are some pictures from the supermarket camera. 

04:26.820 --> 04:30.560
Kenny watches the news. 

04:30.960 --> 04:39.160
The robber is somebody with long blond hair and with a motorcycle.

04:39.220 --> 04:42.200
Says the newsreader. 

04:42.300 --> 04:47.200
Suddenly, Kenny remembers the girl at the motel desk.

04:47.480 --> 04:53.160
Is it her? He thinks. Is she the robber?

05:01.800 --> 05:04.840
Chapter 5. Can I sit here?

05:07.720 --> 05:09.280
He goes for breakfast. 

05:09.380 --> 05:15.580
The girl is eating her breakfast at a table near the window.

05:16.680 --> 05:19.000
Kenny looks at her. 

05:19.100 --> 05:22.000
Is it her? He thinks. 

05:22.100 --> 05:29.200
I think I know her, but he walks across to her table.

05:30.520 --> 05:33.160
Can I sit here? He asks. 

05:33.260 --> 05:41.000
The girl looks up. Well... OK, she says.

05:41.800 --> 05:45.120
Kenny sits down. 

05:45.220 --> 05:55.000
My name's Kenny, he says. Pleased to meet you, she says. I'm Mel.

05:56.120 --> 06:07.240
Where are you from? asks Kenny. San Francisco, says Mel. I'm going there later this morning.

06:08.120 --> 06:16.920
Where are you from? Boston, says Kenny. I'm going across America by bus.

06:18.120 --> 06:25.480
And I'm going to San Francisco later this morning, too. Are you? the girl says.

06:27.000 --> 06:30.920
I don't like buses. I like motorcycles.

06:31.800 --> 06:40.760
Look, excuse me. I need to make a phone call. She gets up and leaves the room.

06:49.000 --> 06:52.200
Chapter 6. Not the police.

06:53.080 --> 07:03.320
A young man near the door is watching Mel. Why is he watching her? thinks Kenny.

07:03.320 --> 07:11.320
Does he know her face, too? Is he thinking she's the girl from the robbery, too?

07:11.320 --> 07:16.120
Kenny goes to sit next to the young man.

07:16.120 --> 07:28.040
Hi, he says. My name's Kenny Muir. Hi, says the young man. I'm Ned.

07:30.040 --> 07:39.880
They begin talking. Kenny tells Ned about the news of the robbery on TV. He looks across at Mel.

07:40.120 --> 07:45.960
Are you thinking that's the same girl? He asks Ned.

07:47.960 --> 07:57.240
Ned looks across at her. I don't know, he says. Perhaps it is.

07:59.560 --> 08:09.480
What can we do? says Kenny. She's leaving soon. Let's phone the police. I think it's her.

08:10.680 --> 08:17.240
No! Ned says quickly. Not the police. Wait.

08:19.160 --> 08:29.000
Kenny looks carefully at him. What's the matter? Are you afraid of something? He asks.

08:31.080 --> 08:37.720
No, but perhaps she's got a gun! says Ned.

08:40.760 --> 08:42.520
I'm sorry.

08:46.680 --> 08:49.960
Chapter 7. Perhaps I'm wrong.

08:53.000 --> 09:03.160
Is it her? thinks Kenny. I want to know. Perhaps the money from the robbery is in her room.

09:03.960 --> 09:14.760
Kenny goes upstairs. Suddenly, he sees the girl again. She is coming out of room 17.

09:16.680 --> 09:22.680
Kenny watches her. She locks her door and goes downstairs.

09:24.680 --> 09:28.520
How can I get into her room? He thinks.

09:29.400 --> 09:32.840
Then Kenny sees a woman working in the motel.

09:34.440 --> 09:46.280
Excuse me, says Kenny. Can you open the door of my room? My key's in the car. It's room 17.

09:47.720 --> 09:54.360
Yes, of course, she says, and opens the door of room 17.

09:55.240 --> 10:01.640
Thank you, says Kenny, and he goes into the room.

10:04.280 --> 10:10.200
Kenny searches the room, but he cannot find the money from the robbery.

10:12.680 --> 10:22.440
Perhaps I'm wrong about her, he thinks. Then he hears somebody opening the door with a key.

10:23.320 --> 10:25.320
It's Mel!

10:40.280 --> 10:43.640
Chapter 8. I must get away.

10:46.040 --> 10:48.040
Kenny runs into the bathroom.

10:48.040 --> 10:54.200
A minute later, he hears Mel talking into the phone.

10:56.520 --> 11:05.960
Hi, Fran, says Mel. No, I'm at the motel. No, I'm leaving in an hour.

11:07.480 --> 11:09.080
Yes, OK.

11:11.640 --> 11:17.240
Kenny looks out carefully from the bathroom. He cannot get to the door.

11:18.120 --> 11:22.600
But he can get to the window. He moves quickly.

11:24.920 --> 11:29.720
Mel puts down the phone. Kenny watches her through the window.

11:31.720 --> 11:35.400
I must get away from here! he thinks.

11:37.800 --> 11:45.960
Kenny cannot go back into room 17, but he can open the window to room 18.

11:48.760 --> 11:50.760
I must get away from here.

11:54.200 --> 11:57.480
Chapter 9. You're the robber.

12:00.120 --> 12:05.560
Kenny climbs into room 18. There is nobody there.

12:07.880 --> 12:13.240
He goes across to the door, but then he sees something.

12:14.200 --> 12:21.080
What's that? He thinks. Is it a wig?

12:22.360 --> 12:25.480
It is. It's a blond wig!

12:27.960 --> 12:29.480
Kenny searches the room.

12:31.560 --> 12:36.040
Here's a black motorcycle coat, he says to himself.

12:36.200 --> 12:44.120
And what's this in this bag? The money from the robbery!

12:46.520 --> 12:53.400
Kenny hears somebody coming. He wants to get out of the room, but he cannot.

12:55.400 --> 13:00.040
Ned comes into the room. He sees Kenny.

13:00.840 --> 13:04.040
What are you doing in my room? says Ned.

13:05.160 --> 13:05.800
Then he sees the blond wig and the money.

13:07.960 --> 13:11.320
He looks at Kenny again.

13:12.840 --> 13:14.360
You know! says Ned.

13:16.360 --> 13:18.600
Yes, I know! says Kenny. You're the Los Angeles supermarket robber!

13:20.280 --> 13:27.960
Suddenly, Ned takes a gun from his coat.

13:30.520 --> 13:33.880
Don't move! he says, and he takes the bag from Kenny.

13:35.560 --> 13:41.320
You can't get away, says Kenny.

13:43.880 --> 13:46.840
Yes, I can, says Ned.

13:48.520 --> 13:51.800
He hits Kenny on the head.

13:53.640 --> 13:55.320
Then he locks him in room 18.

14:08.200 --> 14:11.400
Chapter 10. I can't swim.

14:14.120 --> 14:19.080
A minute later, Mel is looking across at the river from her room.

14:20.840 --> 14:23.960
Suddenly, she sees a man running.

14:26.120 --> 14:31.800
What's the matter with him? She thinks. Why is he running?

14:34.040 --> 14:37.400
Then she sees Kenny come out of the next room.

14:40.520 --> 14:43.000
That man! says Kenny.

14:44.600 --> 14:49.800
He's the Los Angeles supermarket robber! Stop him, somebody!

14:50.600 --> 14:53.880
Ned hears him, and looks up.

14:54.920 --> 15:00.520
Then he gets on his motorcycle and drives off quickly.

15:02.200 --> 15:05.800
I can stop him, says Mel.

15:08.120 --> 15:10.600
She climbs down from her room.

15:11.800 --> 15:16.040
She runs around the motel, gets on her motorcycle,

15:17.000 --> 15:18.840
and goes after Ned.

15:21.320 --> 15:25.160
Mel rides her motorcycle quickly towards the river.

15:26.920 --> 15:31.560
When she gets to the river, she jumps across the river

15:32.360 --> 15:36.680
on the motorcycle and stops in front of Ned.

15:38.200 --> 15:43.560
He cannot stop, and his motorcycle goes into the river.

15:46.600 --> 15:52.920
Help! Help! He cries. I can't swim!

16:02.360 --> 16:06.360
Chapter 11. Can we go slowly, please?

16:08.440 --> 16:11.160
Some people help Ned out of the water.

16:12.920 --> 16:15.080
More people are coming from the motel.

16:17.000 --> 16:18.920
Kenny runs across to Mel.

16:20.840 --> 16:23.400
Are you OK? He asks her.

16:25.400 --> 16:28.280
Yes, I'm OK, she says.

16:29.720 --> 16:30.760
Are you all right?

16:32.520 --> 16:35.720
Yes, says Kenny. I'm all right.

16:38.120 --> 16:42.200
Soon after, the police arrive and take Ned away.

16:42.920 --> 16:45.560
Kenny tells a policeman his story.

16:46.520 --> 16:50.520
Then, Mel tells the policewoman her story.

16:51.960 --> 16:55.960
Do I know your face? The policewoman asks Mel.

16:57.160 --> 16:58.600
Are you famous?

16:59.960 --> 17:01.320
Mel laughs.

17:02.280 --> 17:04.520
Perhaps you do, she says.

17:05.400 --> 17:07.400
I'm on TV sometimes.

17:07.640 --> 17:15.160
Now I remember you, Kenny says to Mel.

17:17.080 --> 17:20.680
You're Mel Palmer, the famous Stunt Girl!

17:21.800 --> 17:26.600
I see you on Stunt Girls, USA, on TV sometimes.

17:28.760 --> 17:29.640
Mel smiles.

17:31.160 --> 17:34.200
Yes, that's me, she says.

17:34.440 --> 17:40.440
Now, do you want to come to San Francisco on my motorcycle,

17:41.240 --> 17:43.880
or do you want to go on the bus?

17:46.360 --> 17:50.520
I'm coming with you! says Kenny, laughing.

17:52.200 --> 17:55.560
But can we go slowly, please?
